import SubPage from '../layouts/SubPage.astro';
---

<SubPage
  title="elliodelics · privacy"
  description="The elliodelics privacy notice. The site collects nothing. Here is what happens with the two exceptions, email and hosting logs."
  heading="Privacy"
>
  <p class="intro">
    This site collects nothing. No cookies, no trackers, no analytics, no
    forms. Two things still involve personal data, so here is exactly what
    happens with each.
  </p>

  <h2>When you email us</h2>
  <p>
    If you write to <a href="mailto:mike@elliodelics.com">mike@elliodelics.com</a>,
    we process what you send. That means your email address, your name if
    you sign it, and whatever your message contains. We use it for one
    purpose, which is answering you and working with you if it comes to that.
  </p>
  <p>
    Mail is hosted by Proton in Switzerland, which processes it on our
    behalf. Beyond that, your correspondence is not shared with anyone
    unless the law compels it, not added to any list, and not used for
    marketing. We keep it the way any business keeps its correspondence,
    as ordinary business records.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can ask what we hold about you, ask for a correction, or ask for
    deletion at any time by emailing the same address. If you are in the
    EU or the UK, you also have the right to complain to your data
    protection authority.
  </p>

  <h2>Hosting logs</h2>
  <p>
    The site is served by GitHub Pages. GitHub logs visitor IP addresses
    and stores them for security purposes, as described in
    <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/pages/getting-started-with-github-pages/what-is-github-pages#data-collection" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-describedby="privacy-new-tab">GitHub's Pages documentation<span class="ext" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a><span class="sr-only" id="privacy-new-tab">opens in new tab</span>.
    We never see those logs and run no logging of our own.
  </p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    The data controller is Elliotec Software LLC, doing business as
    elliodelics, a United States company run by Mike Elliott. For anything
    about this notice, email
    <a href="mailto:mike@elliodelics.com">mike@elliodelics.com</a>.
  </p>

  <p class="mono reviewed">last reviewed · july 2026</p>
</SubPage>
